metadata.Title: CVE-2016-8601 on Ubuntu 14.04 ESM (trusty) - medium.
metadata.Description: ** REJECT **  DO NOT USE THIS CANDIDATE NUMBER.  ConsultIDs: none.  Reason: This candidate was withdrawn by its CNA.  Further investigation showed that it was not a security issue in a "generally available" software product. Notes: none.

notes.Note: jdstrand> android kernels (flo, goldfish, grouper, maguro, mako and manta) are not supported on the Ubuntu Touch 14.10 and earlier preview kernels linux-lts-saucy no longer receives official support linux-lts-quantal no longer receives official support tyhicks> The reporter was asked to move the discussion to linux-fsdevel but, as of 2016-10-12, I don't see a thread related to this issue henrix> This is not in any released kernel, and gregkh actually asked for this CVE to be invalidated.
